  id: Flexor_carpi_ulnaris_muscle.R
  partName: Flexor carpi ulnaris muscle right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The flexor carpi ulnaris muscles are located along the medial aspect of the canine
    forelimb, originating from the medial epicondyle of the humerus and olecranon
    of the ulna. Inserting onto the accessory carpal bone, they primarily function
    to flex the carpus and stabilize
  - ' the carpal joint during locomotion. These muscles contribute to controlled
    paw placement, weight-bearing, and forelimb mechanics. Injury or inflammation
    can restrict carpal flexibility, cause discomfort, and reduce overall forelimb
    performance.'
